'''''Religious Studies Review''''' (RSR) is the [[Academic journal|journal]] of the [[Council of Societies for the Study of Religion]] (CSSR), which is based at [[Rice University]]. The journal is published quarterly by [[Wiley-Blackwell]]. RSR reviews over 1,000 titles annually in review essays and critical notes.<ref name="ResearchGate">{{cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/journal/0319-485X_Religious_Studies_Review|title=Religious Studies Review|work=[[ResearchGate]]|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>
== History == RSR was wholly produced and distributed by the Council till 2005 when they contracted Wiley-Blackwell to manage those. In 2009, Rice University purchased RSR, while Wiley-Blackwell continued the publishing duties.<ref name="Rice">{{Cite web| title = Scholarly Journals {{!}} Humanities| accessdate = 2018-02-10| url = https://humanities.rice.edu/Research-and-Creative-Works/Scholarly-Journals}}</ref>
