'''Virtual Researcher on Call''' ('''VROC''') is a [[Canada|Canadian]] educational program administered by [[Partners in Research]].  The program connects students with knowledge partners — researchers and professionals — in [[health science|health]] and [[natural sciences]], [[technology]], [[engineering]], and [[mathematics]] ([[STEM fields]]) through [[video conferencing]] and [[podcast|video podcasts]].<ref>[http://www.vroc.ca/video/ VROC Video Podcasts]</ref>

==Video conferencing==
Video conferencing technology is used to connect researchers and professionals in the STEM fields with [[elementary school|elementary]] and [[secondary school]] classrooms for real time, interactive discussion.

==Partners==
VROC is partnered with over 40 universities, colleges and institutions as well as school boards across the country.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.vroc.ca/vroc/en/partner/| title=Partnered Institutions| publisher=VROC| date=30 August 2010| accessdate=1 September 2010}}</ref>

==Funding==
VROC began with a "Reaching Higher" [[government grant|grant]] from the Ontario [[Ministry of Training, Colleges and Universities]] in 2006 under the [[Dalton McGuinty]] government.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://ogov.newswire.ca/ontario/GPOE/2006/04/03/c1712.html?lmatch=&lang=_e.html| title=McGuinty Government Investing in Science Students| author=CNW Group| date=3 April 2006| accessdate=4 September 2010}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>

In 2011, Partners in Research was awarded a nearly million dollar grant from the Federal Economic Development Agency for Southern Ontario to teach southern Ontarian students about careers in science, technology, engineering and mathematics.<ref>[http://www.feddevontario.gc.ca/eic/site/723.nsf/eng/00682.html Government of Canada Supports Science and Tech Programming for Southern Ontario Youth]</ref>

Partners in Research hosts a national annual awards reception and ceremony entitled The PIR National Awards to celebrate Canadian research in the STEM fields.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.pirweb.org/pir/en/pir-event/| title=PIR National Awards| publisher=Partners in Research}}</ref> Proceeds from this evening support the Virtual Researcher On Call Program.

==Recognition==
In 2006 VROC was named a "New and Noteworthy Initiative" by the [[Canadian Education Association]].<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.cea-ace.ca/apps/index.cfm?fuseaction=ini.dspDetails&newsid=9b544723-65bf-6b7c-7d99-97691060d227&year=2006| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100921151908/http://cea-ace.ca/apps/index.cfm?fuseaction=ini.dspDetails&newsid=9b544723-65bf-6b7c-7d99-97691060d227&year=2006| dead-url=yes| archive-date=21 September 2010| title=Virtual Researcher on Call| publisher=Canadian Education Association| date=19 December 2006| accessdate=1 September 2010}} </ref>

VROC was awarded the [[ORION (research and education network)|ORION]] Discovery Award of Merit in 2008.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.orion.on.ca/2010awards/pdf/VROC.pdf| title=2008 ORION Discovery Award of Merit| publisher=ORION| accessdate=1 September 2010}}</ref>

